@@ -0,0 +1,552 @@
+.TH "1" 1
+
+.SH "NAME"
+.PP
+\fBzellij\fP \- run zellij
+
+.SH "DESCRIPTION"
+.PP
+Zellij is a workspace aimed at developers, ops\-oriented people and anyone who
+loves the terminal\. At its core, it is a terminal multiplexer (similar to tmux
+and screen), but this is merely its infrastructure layer\.
+.PP
+Zellij includes a layout system, and a plugin system allowing one to create
+plugins in any language that compiles to WebAssembly\.
+.PP
+To list currently running sessions run: `\f[CR]zellij list\-sessions\fP`
+To attach to a currently running session run: `\f[CR]zellij attach [session\-name]\fP`
+
+.SH "OPTIONS"
+.PP
+Run `\f[CR]zellij \-\-help\fP` to see available flags and subcommamds\.
+
+.SH "CONFIGURATION"
+.PP
+Zellij looks for configuration file in the following order:
+.RS
+.Bl
+.IP 1. 4
+the file provided with \fI\-\-config\fP
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP 2. 4
+under the path provided in \fIZELLIJ_CONFIG_FILE\fP environment variable
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP 3. 4
+the default location (see FILES section)
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP 4. 4
+the system location
+.El
+.RE
+.PP
+Run `\f[CR]zellij setup \-\-check\fP` in order to see possible issues with the
+configuration\.
+
+.SH "LAYOUTS"
+.PP
+Layouts are yaml files which Zellij can load on startup when \fI\-\-layout\fP flag is
+provided\.
+By default Zellij will load a layout called `\f[CR]default\.yaml\fP`,
+but this can be changed by using the `\f[CR]default_layout: [LAYOUT_NAME]\fP` configuration option\.
+.PP
+For example a file like this:
+.RS
+.PP
+.nf
+\-\-\-
+direction: Vertical
+parts:
+    \- direction: Horizontal
+      split_size:
+        Percent: 50
+      parts:
+        \- direction: Vertical
+          split_size:
+            Percent: 50
+        \- direction: Vertical
+          split_size:
+            Percent: 50
+    \- direction: Horizontal
+      split_size:
+        Percent: 50
+.fi
+.RE
+.PP
+will tell Zellij to create this layout:
+.RS
+.PP
+.nf
++\-\-\-\-\-+\-\-\-\-\-+|     |     |+\-\-\-\-\-+     ||     |     |+\-\-\-\-\-+\-\-\-\-\-+
+.fi
+.RE
+
+.SS "CREATING LAYOUTS"
+.PP
+A layout file is a nested tree structure\. Each node describes either a pane
+(leaf), or a space in which its parts (children) will be created\.
+.PP
+Each node has following fields:
+.RS
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBdirection: <Horizontal / Vertical>\fP \- node's children will be created by a
+split in given direction\.
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBsplit_size:\fP \- this indicates either a percentage of the node's parent's
+space or a fixed size of columns/rows from its parent's space\.
+.RS
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBPercent: <1\-100>\fP
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBFixed: <lines_number/columns_number>\fP
+.El
+.RE
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBplugin: /path/to/plugin\.wasm\fP \- optional path to a compiled Zellij plugin\.
+If indicated loads a plugin into the created space\. For more information see
+PLUGINS section\.
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBdefault_fg: <color>\fP \- set the default foreground color for a pane (e\.g\. `\f[CR]"#00e000"\fP`)\.
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBdefault_bg: <color>\fP \- set the default background color for a pane (e\.g\. `\f[CR]"#001a3a"\fP`)\.
+.El
+.RE
+
+.SH "KEYBINDINGS"
+.PP
+Zellij comes with a default set of keybindings which aims to fit as many users
+as possible but that behaviour can be overridden or modified in user
+configuration files\. The information about bindings is available in the
+\fIkeybinds\fP section of configuration\. For example, to introduce a keybinding that
+will create a new tab and go to tab 1 after pressing 'c' one can write:
+.RS
+.PP
+.nf
+keybinds:
+    normal:
+        \- action: [ NewTab, GoToTab: 1,]
+          key: [ Char: 'c',]
+.fi
+.RE
+.PP
+where "normal" stands for a mode name (see MODES section), "action" part
+specifies the actions to be executed by Zellij (see ACTIONS section) and "key"
+is used to list  keys or key combinations bound to given actions (see KEYS)\.
+.PP
+The default keybinds can be unbound either for a specific mode, or for every mode\.
+It supports either a list of `\f[CR]keybinds\fP`, or a bool indicating that every keybind
+should be unbound:
+.RS
+.PP
+.nf
+keybinds:
+    unbind: true
+.fi
+.RE
+.PP
+Will unbind every default binding\.
+.RS
+.PP
+.nf
+keybinds:
+    unbind: [ Ctrl: 'p']
+.fi
+.RE
+.PP
+Will unbind every default `\f[CR]^P\fP` binding for each mode\.
+.RS
+.PP
+.nf
+keybinds:
+    normal:
+        \- unbind: true
+.fi
+.RE
+.PP
+Will unbind every default keybind for the `\f[CR]normal\fP` mode\.
+.RS
+.PP
+.nf
+keybinds:
+    normal:
+        \- unbind: [ Alt: 'n', Ctrl: 'g']
+.fi
+.RE
+.PP
+Will unbind every default keybind for `\f[CR]n\fP` and `\f[CR]^g\fP` for the `\f[CR]normal\fP` mode\.
+
+.SS "ACTIONS"
+.RS
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBQuit\fP \- quits Zellij
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBSwitchToMode: <InputMode>\fP \- switches to the specified input mode\. See
+MODES section for possible values\.
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBResize: <Direction>\fP \- resizes focused pane in the specified direction
+(one of: Left, Right, Up, Down)\.
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBFocusNextPane\fP \- switches focus to the next pane to the right or below if
+on  screen edge\.
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBFocusPreviousPane\fP \- switches focus to the next pane to the left or above
+if on  screen edge\.
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBSwitchFocus\fP \- left for legacy support\. Switches focus to a pane with the
+next ID\.
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBMoveFocus: <Direction>\fP \-  moves focus in the specified direction (Left,
+Right, Up, Down)\.
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBClear\fP \- clears current screen\.
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBDumpScreen: [File] [\-\-pane\-id <ID>]\fP \- dumps the pane content to a file or STDOUT\.
+If a file path is provided, writes the content to that file\. If omitted, prints the content to STDOUT\.
+If \-\-pane\-id is provided, dumps the specified pane; otherwise dumps the focused pane\.
+<ID> can be a bare integer (eg\. 1), a terminal pane id (eg\. terminal_1) or a plugin pane id (eg\. plugin_1)\.
+A bare integer is equivalent to a terminal pane id with the same number\.
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBDumpLayout: <File>\fP \- dumps the screen in the specified or default file\.
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBEditScrollback\fP \- replaces the current pane with the scrollback buffer\.
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBScrollUp\fP \- scrolls up 1 line in the focused pane\.
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBScrollDown\fP \- scrolls down 1 line in the focused pane\.
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBPageScrollUp\fP \- scrolls up 1 page in the focused pane\.
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBPageScrollDown\fP \- scrolls down 1 page in the focused pane\.
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBToggleFocusFullscreen\fP \- toggles between fullscreen focus pane and normal
+layout\.
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBNewPane: <Direction>\fP \- opens a new pane in the specified direction (Left,
+Right, Up, Down) relative to focus\.
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBCloseFocus\fP \- closes focused pane\.
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBNewTab\fP \- creates a new tab\.
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBGoToNextTab\fP \- goes to the next tab\.
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBGoToPreviousTab\fP \- goes to previous tab\.
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBCloseTab\fP \- closes current tab\.
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBGoToTab: <Index>\fP \- goes to the tab with the specified index number\.
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBDetach\fP \- detach session and exit\.
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBToggleActiveSyncTab\fP \- toggle between sending text commands to all panes
+on the current tab and normal mode\.
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBUndoRenameTab\fP \- undoes the changed tab name and reverts to the previous name\.
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBUndoRenamePane\fP \- undoes the changed pane name and reverts to the previous name\.
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBSetPaneColor\fP \- sets the default foreground and/or background color of a pane\.
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBBreakPaneToNewTab: { pane_id: <ID>, tab_name: <Name> }\fP \- breaks a pane out into a new
+tab\. `\f[CR]pane_id\fP` is optional; when omitted, the invoking client's currently focused pane is used\.
+`\f[CR]tab_name\fP` is optional; when omitted, the new tab has no name\. `\f[CR]<ID\>\fP` can be a bare integer
+(eg\. 1), a terminal pane id (eg\. terminal_1) or a plugin pane id (eg\. plugin_1)\.
+CLI usage: `\f[CR]zellij action break\-pane [\-\-pane\-id <ID\>] [\-\-name <tab\-name\>]\fP`
+.El
+.RE
+
+.SS "KEYS"
+.RS
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBChar: <character>\fP \- a single character with no modifier\.
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBAlt: <character>\fP \- a single character with `\f[CR]Alt\fP` key as modifier\.
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBCtrl: <character>\fP \- a single character with `\f[CR]Ctrl\fP` key as modifier\.
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBF: <1\-12>\fP \- one of `\f[CR]F\fP` keys (usually at the top of the keyboard)\.
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBBackspace\fP
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBLeft / Right / Up / Down\fP \- arrow keys on the keyboard\.
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBHome\fP
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBEnd\fP
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBPageUp / PageDown\fP
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBBackTab\fP \- a backward Tab key\.
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBDelete\fP
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBInsert\fP
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBEsc\fP
+.El
+.RE
+
+.SS "MODES"
+.RS
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBnormal\fP \- the default startup mode of Zellij\. Provides the ability to
+switch to different modes, as well as some quick navigation shortcuts\.
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBlocked\fP \- disables all keybindings except the one that would switch the
+mode to normal (\fIctrl\-g\fP by default)\. Useful when Zellij's keybindings
+conflict with those of a chosen terminal app\.
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBtmux\fP \- provides convenience keybindings emulating simple tmux behaviour
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBpane\fP \- includes instructions that manipulate the panes (adding new panes,
+moving, closing)\.
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBtab\fP \- includes instructions that manipulate the tabs (adding new tabs,
+moving, closing)\.
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBresize\fP \- allows resizing of the focused pane\.
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBscroll\fP \- allows scrolling within the focused pane\.
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBrenametab\fP \- is a "hidden" mode that can be passed to \fISwitchToMode\fP
+action\. It will trigger renaming of a tab\.
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBrenamepane\fP \- is a "hidden" mode that can be passed to \fISwitchToMode\fP
+action\. It will trigger renaming of a pane\.
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+\fBsession\fP \- allows detaching from a session\.
+.El
+.RE
+
+.SH "Theme"
+.PP
+A color theme can be defined either in truecolor, 256 or hex color format\.
+Truecolor:
+.RS
+.PP
+.nf
+fg: [0, 0, 0]
+.fi
+.RE
+.PP
+256:
+.RS
+.PP
+.nf
+fg: 0
+.fi
+.RE
+.PP
+Hex color:
+.RS
+.PP
+.nf
+fg: "#000000"
+bg: "#000"
+.fi
+.RE
+.PP
+The color theme can be specified in the following way:
+.RS
+.PP
+.nf
+themes:
+  default:
+    fg: [0,0,0]
+    bg: [0,0,0]
+    black: [0,0,0]
+    red: [0,0,0]
+    green: [0,0,0]
+    yellow: [0,0,0]
+    blue: [0,0,0]
+    magenta: [0,0,0]
+    cyan: [0,0,0]
+    white: [0,0,0]
+    orange: [0,0,0]
+.fi
+.RE
+.PP
+If the theme is called `\f[CR]default\fP`, then zellij will pick it on startup\.
+To specify a different theme, run zellij with:
+.RS
+.PP
+.nf
+zellij options \-\-theme [NAME]
+.fi
+.RE
+.PP
+or put the name in the configuration file with `\f[CR]theme: [NAME]\fP`\.
+
+.SH "PLUGINS"
+.PP
+Zellij has a plugin system based on WebAssembly\. Any language that can run on
+WASI can be used to develop a plugin\. To load a plugin include it in a layout
+file\. Zellij comes with default plugins included: \fIstatus\-bar\fP, \fIstrider\fP,
+\fItab\-bar\fP\.
+
+.SH "FILES"
+.PP
+Default user configuration directory location:
+.RS
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+Linux: \fI$XDG_HOME/zellij /home/alice/\.config/zellij\fP
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+macOS: \fI/Users/Alice/Library/Application Support/com\.Zellij\-Contributors\.zellij\fP
+.El
+.RE
+.PP
+Default user layout directory location:
+.RS
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+Subdirectory called `\f[CR]layouts\fP` inside of the configuration directory\.
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+Linux: _$XDG_HOME/zellij/layouts /home/alice/\.config/zellij/layouts
+.El
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+macOS: \fI/Users/Alice/Library/Application/layouts Support/com\.Zellij\-Contributors\.zellij/layouts\fP
+.El
+.RE
+.PP
+Default plugin directory location:
+.RS
+.Bl
+.IP \(bu 4
+Linux: _$XDG_DATA_HOME/zellij/plugins /home/alice/\.local/share/plugins
+.El
+.RE
+
+.SH "ENVIRONMENT"
+.PP
+ZELLIJ_CONFIG_FILE
+Path of Zellij config to load\.
+ZELLIJ_CONFIG_DIR
+Path of the Zellij config directory\.
+
+.SH "NOTES"
+.PP
+The manpage is meant to provide concise offline reference\. For more detailed
+instructions please visit:
+.PP
+https://zellij\.dev/documentation
\ No newline at end of file
